        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria",
        "description": "The constitutive model must capture elastic-plastic behavior with isotropic hardening for Ti-6Al-4V. Contact formulation must capture slip/stick behavior at screw-rod interface. Model form uncertainty must be quantified and included in the total uncertainty budget."
      },
      "rationale": "The FEA model employs a bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity model (E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa, E_t=2.3 GPa) for Ti-6Al-4V, consistent with published tensile test data for ELI grade material. The Lagrange multiplier contact formulation captures both stick and slip regimes at the screw-rod interface; a friction coefficient of μ=0.25 was calibrated against independent tribological data. Model form uncertainty was estimated via a Bayesian model comparison between the bilinear hardening model and a Ramberg-Osgood alternative; the Bayes factor of 8.3 favors the bilinear model. Model form uncertainty contribution to total QoI uncertainty: 31% (stiffness), 44% (yield force), 38% (force at 40 mm)."
    },
