        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Testing must be performed under at least two distinct loading configurations (e.g., varying span or offset) to characterize model response across the operating envelope. Achieved Gradation 2 (single loading configuration per ASTM F1717); Gradation 3 would require a second configuration."
      },
      "rationale": "All experimental testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration (40 mm span, standard UHMWPE block fixture). While this configuration is the regulatory standard for pedicle screw constructs and is directly relevant to the COU, only one test condition was employed, limiting the ability to characterize model response across the full operating envelope. This results in an achieved level of Gradation 2 against a required level of Gradation 3. The shortfall is offset by the high consistency between FEA predictions and experimental results (all E/uval < 1.96) and by the conservative nature of the single-condition test (worst-case bending scenario per ASTM F1717). An OffsetRationale is documented in the DecisionRecord."
    },
