      "rationale": "The three validation QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are identical to the quantities cited in the 510(k) regulatory submission claim and in ASTM F1717 Section 9.1 acceptance criteria. A QoI relevance matrix (Document QRI-COU1-v1.2) documents the mapping from each validation QoI to the corresponding clinical failure mode (construct instability → stiffness; screw fracture initiation → yield force; large-deformation integrity → force at 40 mm). All three QoIs are directly measurable in both the FEA model and the physical test, eliminating the need for surrogate quantity mapping."
