        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Validation activity relevance acceptance criteria",
        "description": "The validation test configuration must replicate the COU loading and boundary conditions to within documented similarity criteria. Any deviations from COU conditions must be assessed for their effect on model credibility."
      },
      "rationale": "The ASTM F1717 static compression-bending test is the direct regulatory analog to the in vivo compression-bending loading experienced by lumbar pedicle screw constructs. The test configuration (UHMWPE block simulating vertebral body, 40 mm span representing inter-vertebral distance, axial-bending combined loading) matches the dominant in vivo loading mode. Deviations from in vivo conditions (absence of biological tissue, isothermal vs. physiological temperature, static vs. cyclic loading) are documented in the COU boundary document (CBD-COU1-v2.1) with assessed impact: tissue absence increases conservatism; temperature difference has <1% effect on Ti-6Al-4V properties; static vs. cyclic is addressed by a separate fatigue COU (COU2, not assessed here)."
    }
